{
  "_source": "decode_script.item_commits() (init-routine fix 2026-06-27 p2). ONE item path: op 0x31 in per-room slot-5. K77 (2026-07-10): the id byte is the SAT-1 VM-THREAD SLOT, not a catalog item id -- its item correlation is empirical and the 'randomizer lever' status is UNVERIFIED pending the give-path decode / F1 witness (ITEMS-KEYITEMS-RE-PLAN Phase 2).",
  "_fields": "id=block+0x04 (mode-0 literal = 0x48bf20 `type` = the VM-thread slot; empirically 1:1 with the field item type, mechanism unproven -- K77); param=block+0x00 (the 0x48bf20 `param` arg = rec+0x18 = a ROUTINE INDEX into the slot-5 routine table; routine[param] is the pickup program that decides the granted item -- do NOT shuffle it); slot=block+0x30 (AOT array slot); id_blob_off=byte offset of the id literal in the DECOMPRESSED room blob; op_blob_off=offset of the op-0x31 byte; pos=[X,Z] first corner of the SAT-1 trigger quad (rec+4/rec+6 = block+0x24/+0x20 mode-0 literals; builder 0x489880 maps rec+4..rec+0x12 = 4 signed (X,Z) corners; 2026-07-12). See docs/reference/dc2/doors/AOT-SYSTEM-RE.md (UPDATE banner) + K77/K80.",
